# Cursor Rules for SideGuy Solutions

## Project Overview
This is a static website for SideGuy Solutions, featuring:
- Phantom wallet integration for Solana
- Yield calculator for stablecoin investments
- Custom domain: www.sideguysolutions.com
- Hosted on GitHub Pages

## Code Style & Conventions

### HTML
- Use semantic HTML5 elements (`<header>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<footer>`)
- Always include proper meta tags (viewport, description, charset)
- Use `defer` attribute for non-critical scripts
- Include ARIA labels for accessibility
- Button elements should have `type="button"` to prevent form submission

### CSS
- Use kebab-case for class names (e.g., `wallet-section`, `calc-form`)
- Follow BEM-like naming when appropriate
- Use CSS variables for colors (cosmic-purple theme: #6a1b9a, #8e24aa, #9945FF)
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Include hover states and transitions for better UX

### JavaScript
- Use camelCase for variables and functions
- Always check for element existence before accessing (e.g., `if (element)`)
- Use async/await for asynchronous operations
- Handle errors gracefully with user-friendly messages
- Comment complex logic, especially Solana wallet interactions

## File Structure
```
/
├── index.html          # Main HTML file
├── styles.css          # All styles
├── script.js           # All JavaScript functionality
├── CNAME              # Custom domain configuration
├── README.md          # Project documentation
└── .cursorrules       # This file
```

## Key Technologies
- **Solana Web3.js**: For Phantom wallet integration
- **Vanilla JavaScript**: No frameworks
- **GitHub Pages**: Static hosting

## Important Notes
- The website uses Phantom wallet extension (must be installed in browser)
- Solana Web3.js library is loaded from CDN (unpkg.com)
- Custom domain is configured via CNAME file
- All changes must be pushed to main branch for GitHub Pages deployment

## When Making Changes
1. Test wallet connection functionality locally
2. Ensure all HTML elements referenced in JS exist
3. Verify responsive design on mobile devices
4. Check that Solana Web3.js library is loaded
5. Test calculator with and without wallet connection
6. Commit and push to main branch for auto-deployment

## Common Patterns

### Wallet Connection
```javascript
if (window.solana && window.solana.isPhantom) {
    // Wallet available
}
```

### Error Handling
```javascript
try {
    // async operation
} catch (err) {
    console.error('Error:', err);
    // User-friendly error message
}
```

### Element Access
```javascript
const element = document.getElementById('id');
if (element) {
    // Safe to use element
}
```

## Avoid
- ❌ Inline styles (use CSS classes)
- ❌ Hardcoded API keys or sensitive data
- ❌ Breaking changes without testing
- ❌ Removing CNAME file (breaks custom domain)
- ❌ Using frameworks without necessity (keep it vanilla)

## Testing Checklist
- [ ] Wallet connects successfully
- [ ] Balance loads correctly
- [ ] Calculator works with manual input
- [ ] Calculator works with wallet balance
- [ ] Disconnect functionality works
- [ ] Mobile responsive design
- [ ] All buttons are clickable
- [ ] No console errors

